        <div n="086-304B">
          <head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-086-304B-headnote-1">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-086-304B-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-086-304B-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">&#13;</l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-086-304B-headnote-2">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-086-304B-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-086-304B-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-086-304B-headnote-3">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-086-304B-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-086-304B-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-1" n="1">When Mother Clud had rise from play,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-2" n="2">And call'd to take y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Cards away.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-3" n="3">Van saw, but seem'd not to regard,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-4" n="4">How Miss pick'd ev'ry painted Card;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-5" n="5">And buisy both with hand, and Eye,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-6" n="6">Soon rear'd a house two Storys high.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-7" n="7">Van's Genious without thought or Lecture,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-8" n="8">This hugely turn'd to Architecture;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-9" n="9">He saw y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Edifice, and smil'd,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-10" n="10">Vow'd it was pretty for a child.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-11" n="11">It was so perfect in its kind,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-12" n="12">He kept y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Modell in his Mind;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-13" n="13">But when he found y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Boys at play,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-14" n="14">And saw them dabling in their Clay,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-15" n="15">He Stood behind a Stall, to Lurk,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-16" n="16">And mark y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Progress of their work</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-17" n="17">With true delight observ'd y<hi rend="superscript">m</hi> all,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-18" n="18">Raking up Mudd to build a Wall.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-19" n="19">The Plan he much admir'd, and took</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-20" n="20">The Modell in his table Book,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-21" n="21">Thought him self now exactly Skill'd;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-22" n="22">And so resolv'd a house to build.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-23" n="23">A real house with Rooms, &amp; Stairs,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-24" n="24">Five times, at least, as big as theirs.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-25" n="25">Taller than Misses by two yards,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-26" n="26">Not a sham thing of Clay, or Cards.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-27" n="27">And so he did; for in a while</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-28" n="28">He built up such a Monstrous Pile</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-29" n="29">That no two Chair-men could be found</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-30" n="30">Able to lift it from y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Ground.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-31" n="31">Still at White Hall it stands in View,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-32" n="32">Just in y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> place where first it Grew.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-33" n="33">There all y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> little School Boys run,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-34" n="34">Envying to see them selves out done</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-35" n="35">From such deep Rudiments as these,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-36" n="36">Van is become by due degrees</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-37" n="37">For building fam'd, &amp; Justly reckon'd</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-38" n="38">At Court Vitruvious y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> second.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-39" n="39">No wonder since wise Authors shew,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-40" n="40">That best foundations must be so;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-41" n="41">And now y<hi rend="superscript">e</hi> Duke has wisely ta'en him</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-42" n="42">To be his Architect at Bleinheim;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-43" n="43">But railery for once apart,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-44" n="44">If this Rule holds in Ev'ry art</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-45" n="45">Or if his Grace was no more skilld in,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-46" n="46">The art of Battering Walls, than Building;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-47" n="47">We might expect to find next Year</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-086-304B-line-48" n="48">A mouse Trap-Man Chief Engineer.</l>
          </lg>
